{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4fcfcbfe-200e-4490-a136-7c8462f474b3","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic async Task MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\n**Key difference:** xUnit embeds the skip reason directly in `[Fact]`/`[Theory]` via the `Skip` property, while the others use a separate attribute.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"330d76d6-3c31-42ec-98d8-5f415b7e1b5a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without tools.","outputTokens":319,"requestId":"9820:3C606F:19DB33:2218C0:69FFDC0D"},"id":"e6992f18-ef0a-4dbe-91f3-5b5d1206ab2b","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:14:59.828Z","parentId":"60b7d224-9b2e-43c6-9515-215373b62076"}
